# shellcheck shell=bash
# config.local.env.example -- copy to config.local.env (gitignored), then edit:
#
#     cp config.local.env.example config.local.env
#
# This file is EXECUTED (sourced) by _aws-env.sh, not parsed as data -- treat it as
# trusted shell, like the scripts themselves; do not paste untrusted snippets.
#
# Sourced BEFORE config.env, so values set here override the committed defaults in
# config.env. An explicit env var on the command line still wins over both -- that is
# why the assign-if-unset form `: "${VAR:=...}"` is used here too: it preserves the
# documented one-off override `BUDGET_EMAIL=... scripts/deploy.sh`.
#
# Every line below is COMMENTED so a bare `cp` of this template does NOT satisfy the
# required BUDGET_EMAIL -- uncomment and set a real value. (Leaving it commented keeps
# deploy.sh's `: "${BUDGET_EMAIL:?}"` guard the enforcement point.) Placeholders are
# RFC-2606 reserved (example.com) / zero-account ARNs, so the committed .example never
# carries a real secret.

# REQUIRED -- the Budgets alarm subscriber address. Uncomment and set yours:
# : "${BUDGET_EMAIL:=you@example.com}"

# Optional -- the IAM role allowed to invoke the slice-3 IAM-auth query Function URL.
# Left unset, deploy.sh defaults it to the deploying caller's own role ARN.
# : "${INVOKER_ROLE_ARN:=arn:aws:iam::000000000000:role/YourDeployRole}"

# Optional -- override committed defaults from config.env:
# : "${AWS_REGION:=us-east-1}"
# : "${DEPLOY_DEPARTMENT:=platform}"
# : "${STACK:=GraphragSlice1}"
